            "subject": "LU-4702 nodemap: fix nm_rbtree_postorder_for_each_entry_safe()"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Bobi Jam",
          "email": "bobijam.xu@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-02-13 15:27:41.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-03-10 23:40:56.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-4627 llite: deed taking lli_trunc_sem during file write",
        "message": "LU-4627 llite: deed taking lli_trunc_sem during file write\n\nFile write before io loop will take lli_trun_sem read semaphore to\nprotect osc_extent, while after generic_file_aio_write() done, it\ncould possible need to kill suid or sgid, which will call\nll_setattr_raw() to change the inode's attribute, and it does not\ninvolve size.\n\nSo the ll_truc_sem write semaphore should be constrained\naround ll_setattr_ost() to not come across the lli_trunc_sem read\nsemaphore get from the normal file write path.\n\nSigned-off-by: Bobi Jam <bobijam.xu@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ic7f9cfb6d76dcf7ad08635efab154e7cdc392ce8\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/9267\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: Jinshan Xiong <jinshan.xiong@intel.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Lai Siyao <lai.siyao@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
